caption: Oishi, delicious Sheena excellent customer service! Would be 5 stars but parking not so good and a bit pricey. We look forward to going again!
Great vibe, good service, excelent food.

The sushi was pretty good and standard I think.  They definitely did not amaze me for the price that you are paying.   However their appetizers and small dishes are really.   Only thing I didn't like was the fried chicken!   It was bland and didn't come with any sauce.

My top 3 sushi restaurants (not including omakase only sushi restaurants) I have ever been in the USA/Hawaii. This place is so underrated. Friendly staff and great bar seating omakase experience and of course very fresh ingredients. They also have unique and rare imported fishes and seafood from Japan. Come here and try their omakase if you have that adventurous pallet but not recommended for someone that just wants spicy tuna, california roll, salmon, yellowfin on the omakase menu. This place has kama-toro and this was the first time the chef introduced us to this phenomenon toro cut. They also have santa Barbara and hokkaido uni.
Amazing! Super fresh fish. Perch and O-toro were out of this world.

(Translated by Google) It was very delicious. This may be the most delicious Japanese food I ate in Hawaii. Itamae is Japanese, you can see the real taste!  (Original) とても美味しかったです。ハワイで食べた日本料理の中、ここは一番美味しいかも。板前は日本人です、本番の味わかります！
(Translated by Google) The sashimi, fried chicken and scallops, and the scallops were all delicious.  (Original) お刺身、かぼちやの唐揚げ、ホタテの中トロまきなど、どれもおいしかったです。
Friendly staff, great chiefs and excellent food.
excellent Food and service. Pick up orders are Fantastic!
This place sets the bar so high that is unreal. A must go. Great service and fun
Fresh sushi that melt in your mouth.
-Absolutely great! Very fresh,  very authentic, very tasty! -Upscale price wise. - You need reservation to be seated
Great service and Food was fresh and top quality

loving every dish except the monkfish liver. The fish is fresh and the dishes are really creative. Specifically  love the chu Toro nigiri, miso butter fish, baked king crab, tomago. As we sat at the sushi bar, I saw a chef made shaomai from the scratch!!!
My favorite restaurant in Honolulu. Great food and sake, friendly staff.
(Translated by Google) A sushi restaurant with high quality.  (Original) qualityが高いお寿司屋さんです。
Overpriced and unfriendly staff.

An excellent place to get some high quality sushi. The fish was of top quality and came through in the form of texture and flavor.  We were lucky enough to get there right as they opened so we were able to be seated without a reservation. That being said I would definitely recommend making a reservation a few days in advance. In terms of parking we heard that parking was limited so we took an Uber from our hotel, I would recommend the same so that you have a more enjoyable time.  As I said the food was amazing, we opted for the chefs choice omakasi nigiri, the one where they keep bringing out the nigiri till you say stop. We spent about $265 for two people which included 12 pieces of sashimi per person, two tamago, one roll and one custard. All of the food was amazing and it was quite the experience tasing a few fish that neither myself or wife had ever tried before. It is a pricey experience but if you are sharing a special event (for myself it was the last night of my honeymoon) then go for it! We personally did not regret it!
(Translated by Google) Honolulu You can enjoy fresh sashimi  (Original) 호노룰루 신선한 회를 즐길수 있어요
Food is good. Service is below average....
Go there, just fcing go there. SO GOOD!

Honolulu, and especially the Waikiki area, is littered with sushi restaurants but my recommendation is to go the extra distance and eat here!! We went Omakase and feasted on the chefs best offerings. The rice was perfect, the fish was fresh and had some great options I hadn’t seen before.

This place is mind blowingly delicious. Hands down the best sushi selection in the Bay Area. They always have fresh delicious uni at lunch time and the best Omakase I have ever had. Everyone should experience the sushi served at Sushi Izakaya Gaku. If you were not a sushi lover before you would be after. I am so thankful for having this place around.
Great taste and service

(Translated by Google) I was able to enjoy a lot more delicious food than the price I had at the famous steak house. Sushi, rolls, garragas and grilled fish were excellent. Next time we go to Hawaii, we will visit again.  (Original) 유명 스테이크 하우스에서 먹었던거 보다 가격대비 훨씬 더 다양하게 맛있게 식사를 즐길수 있었습니다. 스시, 롤, 가라게, 생선구이 등 훌륭했습니다. 다음에 하와이에 가면 재방문할 예정입니다.
As always fresh fish and awesome food!
Good sushi
Great sushi
Taste buds on fire at this place! Top quality fish and preparation. Gaku won’t disappoint for an amazing sushi dinner.
Honestly the best fish I've ever had in my life! We got the omakaze nagiri style. Incredible. Also the crab cake was delicious and succulent.
Good food, but a bit expensive.

(Translated by Google) A taxi from Waikiki, a Japanese sake, and a shochu brand in the vicinity of Ala Moana shopping center Although it is a Japanese tavern style, three people alone 25000 yen Do not drink alcohol only for meals, sashimi and sushi are expensive? Please be careful with the price and eat it.  (Original) アラモアナショッピングセンターの近くでワイキキからタクシー、日本酒、焼酎銘柄多く日本の居酒屋風だが、３人で25000円お酒は飲まず食事だけ、刺身や寿司は高いかな？価格に要注意して召し上がって下さい。
One of our favorite Japanese places on the island. Fresh fish. Tasty dishes. Be sure to call and make reservations at least 1 week in advance. They also don’t do take out

The first time I was here was more than 8 years ago, and I'm happy to say it's just as good as I remember. It's kind of hidden and has a very small parking lot, but you can find some street parking nearby. The area it's in does get a bit sketchy later at night. They dont take reservations after 7pm and even then it's only for 4 less people and they go quickly. The food is very fresh and very good, you can eat alot of different dishes and then still be willing to eat more. Anything seafood related would be the best bet. Sashimi,  butterfish, and seafood dynamite are especially good. They have bar seating, tables up front, and a few larger tables in the back for parties of 4.
Closed even though their physical sign for this business hours online said they were open. Imaginary sushi is worse than bad sushi.
Scrumptious options, fresh selections and solid sake list. Lovely customer service and cozy space. I wish we had this place in Seattle! <3

My wife brought me here for my birthday.  We got the sashimi plate (for 2).  While delicious, it was not enough really for 2 people, so we got a salad, some butterfish and some extra toro.  All were delicious, but we definitely had more room for desserts, which were tasty as well.  In all, it was a good sushi experience and the restaurant deserves its good reputation.
Exceptional Japanese cuisine with comfortable upscale Izakaya atmosphere

This is the best sushi place you must go in Oahu. Fresh fish, Tasty and good quality. I really like to siting at the sushi counter because the sushi chefs will recommend things to you and I enjoy to look at they making. They’re really care for every plate. 😃 I love Hiyashi Shiratanta Zenzai ( Cold sweet azuki beans with mochi balls)
Friendly staff, delicious food
Always a good meal here. Never disappointed.  Otoro the best. Seared Garlic Toro even better.
Very very good. Little small but cozy. I don't know where to park tho.

What a meal this was. We wanted to try everything on the menu and were so full when we left. Parking is hard to find and we parked a bit away on a side street. Inside, there were regular tables and the sunken tables where you take off your shoes at the stairs. We tried a little bit of everything, sushi, udon, their apps the waitress recommended. We would come back if we are ever back in the area.
Great food.  Good selection.  Easy to find a seat if you arrive as soon as they open.

if your thing is tuna avo rolls, you can get them here. but the people who will really appreciate Gaku are the ones who not only order otoro but aji, kohada, sting ray, the house made bone chips, and the thinly sliced fresh ginger that they obtain from the Big Island.
Fine delicacies in cozy setting

(Translated by Google) Subete totemo oishikattadesu!  (Original) Subete totemo oishikattadesu!
4 really old Asian peeps were waiting outside & were super excited to be there...knew it was a good sign. Holy bejeezus...some of the best stuff. I have no idea what I was eating but it was SO good.
Inventive and delicious Izakaya
The sushi was ok, but the hamachi tartar was amazing.

A friend recommended dinner here for sushi, so glad we made the trip out and waited for a table! Shared a bunch of dishes, the hamachi tartare appetizer was outstanding, spicy salmon roll and tuna roll were yummy. I will say the price here was a bit expensive, but the service and food quality were very good and worth the steep cost... For a special occasion!
While the food here is quite normal, the setting is just amazing

It’s totally rip off place...tastes good but not good enough to pay that price.. staff are friendly but the man standing behind the counter is not, even looks angry... Why? Who knows? Absolute rip off place.. If there is 0 point, I would give it.
Some of the best sushi in town.

Amazing sushi and sashimi.  The key is to sit at the sushi bar and have the omakase and the second omakase- which is ongoing sushi selected by the chef until you say ‘stop’.  High quality food. I’d definitely go back.

Sushi selection was very good and uni shooter was executed well. The sushi wouldnt have made this a five star but the daily special of pork was really amazing and is what made me value it as high. The daily dessert was cheesecake which was okay. First sushi restaurant in hawaii! More to follow.
The best sushi in America.
Good quality fish, however super small pieces for the price. I left starving and spent $65 without tip! Service was good with everyone being happy and friendly.
Lacks flavor. Not the best izakaya restaurant
Best sushi in Hawaii
Food and service both are excellent.

Seriously disappointed after all these reviews, my husband and I were shocked and upset that the man at the entrance refused to sit us when there was plenty of space, tables free and space at the bar. We called several hours before the same day and the man said they don't take reservations after 7pm and it's walk-in first come first serve but when we asked for table for two, they were "holding" tables for people on the way. It felt like we are refused to sit because of not being Japanese. Hope we are wrong.

Rip off place... Who would charge $35 for a rainbow roll??? We asked for a rainbow roll which wasn't on their menu but they said they could do it. Never gave us heads up about the price considering they don't have anything over $20 on their menu. when we asked why their waitress replied "we use good fish"!!! Their other rolls were microscopic in comparison with other places. Absolute rip off place 😠

Authentic and Fresh! I have been coming here for years and it is still my favorite Sushi Bar on the island. LOVE everything here especially the uni shooter which is a must have for me whenever I eat here. Parking: Free behind the building Price: it's pretty up there but so worth it Reservations: If it's just the both of you then, you may get lucky to be seated right away. But if you have a group/family then I recommend you make reservations.
Absolutely fantastic food, super friendly staff-entire sushi bar greets you. Worth the price.
Good fresh fish here, sushi and sake are always a delight
Very good food and outstanding service.
Truly authentic  Japanese food.
Food is good, quite busy on Saturday evenings. Recommend making reservations. Although they do take walkins at around 730pm. Service could be better.
Awesome food.

Surprised! I did not write a review for this place??!! Manabu-san does really good job! I usually order: Oysters are always good and fresh! Assorted Sashimi is a good deal! "MP" scares me but I would like to try some MP menus next time!
Staff is friendly and can easily explain everything in the menu. Food was very good and the price was a bit high, but it is Hawaii.

Amazing creations for izakaya. The wagyu nigiri would be almost commonplace while things like the mushroom salad and king crab cakes would take you to that next level of izakaya nirvana. Stop by to up level your game.
I've never had a bad experience here. From the food to the service it's always been good. If they have akamatsu, definitely get some nigiri and the steak is 95% of time cooked to perfection.

I always enjoying going here.  Great food and pleasant staff.  I'm vegetarian and last time I went, they ran out of steamed vegetables by 8pm. WOW!   Other than that, normally great place!  Just make sure you reserve two day in advance, especially if you want a table.  Counter can open up but getting a table is a bit harder.
Traditional Japanese izakaya. Tough to get a seat, not really a baby friendly place. Don't listen to the other reviewer who says to go to Nobu. That's sacrilege.
The Omakase was great. The food and ambiance are traditional Japanese.

This is a way over priced sushi restaurant with small portions and terrible presentation for the money. If you wanna spend this type of money go to nobu for way better food and service. Also the restaurant is not that nice either.  Try the tea they serve and that will set the tone on what the quality will be... Don't bother go somewhere else ... This is a tourist trap place

We have been to this restaurant twice and each time we were blown away.  They have the best service, the best sushi we have had anywhere in Hawaii.  They also have other dishes that are worth trying, simply because they are all so delicious!  We fly over to Oahu several times every years and this restaurant will always be top on our list.  The Sushi Chefs are wonderful and very professional.  We'll be back time after time.

Maybe we ordered the wrong things, but not the most impressed considering the accolades that Gaku gets.  The menu is also a bit too extensive - I'd rather see them excel at a more concentrated list of things.

My friends and I have been to most of the restaurant on this island.  I would say this place probably has the best sushi and delicious appetizer (uni shooter).  However, we all agree that the service we experienced was also the worst by far.  When we went in everything was great at first.  But after our appetizer were served, we did not see our server for almost an hour.  There were no refills and no explanation for the delay of main course.  We sat and watch people came in after us and getting their food before us.  Eventually we grabbed our server and expressed our frustrations.  The server offered no compensations and worst of all, no apologies. 5 stars food, 2 stars service

I ate here last night with three friends. It is traditional Japanese seating, that is remove your shoes. We spend $500 with tip. Two bottles of sake, 4 beers, a few entrees, and many sushi later... The fish was fresh.  The service was good. I would recommend this place.
This place is amazing.
Delicious, almost like Sasabune, but more affordable, and broader selection. Definitely, a recommend.
Gaku is probably the most authentic izakaya in Honolulu. Never disappointing. A little pricey but anything really great is.  EXCELLENT
All time favorite on Oahu.  Such beautiful fish and impeccable service!  This is the real deal.  Just take a look at the crispy fried fish bones for the asking above the chefs at the bar.  Exquisite!
Wow! Best sushi experience. Do make sure you call ahead and make a reservation. Otherwise be prepared to wait an hour or so. The sashimi is fresh, providing a very simple yet refreshing flavor.

Great food, wonderful staff and chef.  Price is a bit high for portion sizes (tiny), but food is excellent!
